  <h2>The Discipline is:</h2>
  <p>suspension from the bus and  transportation is not listed on my child’s IEP.</p>
  </div>
  <h2>Response:</h2>
  <p>A suspension from the bus is not a change of placement and  does not count as a removal of a child from school provided the child:</p>
  <ol>
  <li>is given services that allow him or her  to continue to appropriately progress in the general curriculum </li>
  <li>continues to receive the services  specified in his or her IEP, <em>and</em></li>
  <li>continues to participate with children  without disabilities to the extent</li>
  </ol>
  <p>he or she would have in his or her  current placement. For example, if your child was in the regular education classroom,  he or she must be assigned to the same in-school suspension room as children  without disabilities.</p>
  <h2>Options:</h2>
  <p>If the above conditions are not met, then the bus suspension  should be treated as an out-of-school suspension. </p>
  <p><a href="#">Go To Out-of-School Suspensions</a> </p>
  <p class="tip">Tip: If the behavior on the bus is similar to the behavior in  school that is already addressed by an IEP, you should request an IEP meeting  to discuss addressing the bus behavior in your child’s IEP and Behavioral  Intervention Plan (BIP).</p>
